<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-22004] Kafka component shutdown may get stuck when rebalancing occurs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-22004</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://camel.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/257298-camel/topic/Kafka.20component.20fails.20to.20shutdown.20after.20repartitioning&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Zulip chat thread&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;KafkaFetchRecords instance holds a reference to the Consumer from kafka-clients. When the rebalancing event occurs after the pause call has already been issued (as a part of doSuspend call in KafkaConsumer), the topic partition states which are held in the SubscriptionState object inside of kafka-clients Consumer instance are replaced by the new assignment and the pause flag is therefore lost.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Kafka component may then be stuck in accepting new messages (notifying about pending exchanges) instead of finishing current processing and completing the shutdown.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
